# PodCut core standards

These conventions apply in any editor or tooling. They align with [docs/STANDARDS.md](docs/STANDARDS.md) and keep the codebase maintainable and testable.

## Performance

- Avoid O(n²) work on large media, frame arrays, or long timelines. Prefer single passes, maps, or bounded windows.
- Load heavy WASM (FFmpeg, MediaPipe, ONNX, VAD) **lazily** (dynamic import / on-demand init), never on the critical path of first paint.

## Type safety

- TypeScript `strict` is mandatory. **Do not use `any`** — ESLint treats `@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any` as **error**.
- Prefer descriptive domain types (`MediaFileId`, seconds as named types) over anonymous primitives where it clarifies contracts.

## Zustand / state

- Updates must be **immutable** — use functional `set((state) => ({ ... }))` and shallow copies; never mutate nested objects in place.
- App-wide mutations must go through the composed store in [src/app/store/index.ts](src/app/store/index.ts); **`stateValidator` must not be bypassed** (see [src/app/store/middleware/stateValidator.ts](src/app/store/middleware/stateValidator.ts)).

## Logging

- `no-console` is **warn** with only `console.warn` and `console.error` allowed without tripping the rule. Avoid `console.log` in committed code.

## Complexity (ESLint)

- **Cyclomatic complexity** ≤ 10 per function.
- **Nesting depth** ≤ 4 — extract helpers or early returns instead of deeper nesting.

## Tests and documentation

- New complex pure logic should get coverage via `src/test/harness/` and `npm run test:harness`.
- Prefer recording non-trivial design decisions under `docs/` (see [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md)).
